  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWe extract all transaction data for each block from Ethereum using JSON-RPC, then we iterate through all receipts and assemble the data before saving it to the database. However, I found that when retrieving transaction receipts, they are also obtained one block at a time, cached, and then metadata is added. If we have an interface that returns both the block's receipt and metadata together, it would be much more efficient for the client.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature? // yes\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature? // yes\r\n\r\n\r\nSimilar issues:\r\n\r\n- https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/17044\r\n ",
